No longer relevant.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b>      PoP suggested changes:</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>
I haven't had a chance to analyze all the spells for this expansion in depth, but after a moderately careful look over the spell list Wizard Draughts seem very lacking.  For non-EER/GSS Wizards (which is the catagory most lvl 60 Wizards currently fall into) they must wait all the way until 64 to get a really shining nuke.  This is assuming that AT will be buyable/easily attainable (which is the usual pattern for nukes prior to the last lvl of an expansion).  Tenatively, PoP Draughts should have their damage increased accross the board--at least enough for the PoP Cold Draught to still be better than the Kunark Cold Draught when using EI (EI only effects spells upto lvl 60).<br>
<br>
I would still very much like to see a higher damage Mage nuke at lvl 60, but with the addition of PoP spells I don't see room for this to happen.  Firebolt of Tallon is a superb spell, but only a slight damage increase over SFoS.  There isn't any room to increase the damage of SFoS without trivializing FoT.  Damage and mana could be increased on FoT, but that would keep it an outstanding ratio spell, while also improving it's DPS significantly, which would then cheapen Sun Vortex.  The whole situation is very tricky and probably best left as is.  If Magi want to be nukers, buy PoP.  You only have to make one more level (from 60) to get FoT, so the insult known as Moonfire won't sting for too long.<br>
<br>
This expansion seems to put more focus on Druids as healers, rather than nukers--hooray for VI!  As long as Druid healing power is sufficient to make them viable in groups and on raids, I think their DoT debuffs combine with their new nukes will do all right as far as damage.  If Druids turn out to be inadequate as healers, than their nukes need some looking at, as they are really quite gimpy.  VI could solve a lot of balance issues by retuning Moonfire to be more reasonable, considering how easy it is to get.<br>
<br>
Jeebus, what's up with Insanity?  This change would put it right between Dementing Visions and the 'chanter Ancient, ratio-wise.<br>
<br>
